extra.message: Affected versions of aiohttp are vulnerable to Improper Input Validation. The vulnerability arises when inadequate validation allows an attacker to manipulate HTTP requests, including modifying headers or crafting new requests when controlling the HTTP version, particularly evident when the Connection header is directed to the headers parameter, enabling CRLF injection by bypassing validation when a list is passed.

Affected versions of aiohttp are vulnerable to Improper Limitation Of A Pathname To A Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal'). Improperly configuring static resource resolution in aiohttp when used as a web server  using `follow_symlinks=True` can result in the unauthorized reading of arbitrary files on the system as there is no  validation to check if a given file path is within the root directory.

cwe: CWE-22: Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')
